

=Description=

Anthony D'Onofrio:

"This is the PPI (Persistent Pseudonymous Identity) component of the network. Your DAI is the store for your transactions, reputation, and other data on the network. It ostensibly represents one individual human actor, but in practice could actually be multiple. It is pseudonymous in that it need not map 1 to 1 with your real-world identity, and persistent in that you use it over time to build a reputation. A single individual must not necessarily have only one DAI, and in fact may have many, and likely will, as this is reflective of the manner with which we tend to wear many hats. The DAI is not a required component to utilize DApps or DAO's, but without PPI it is difficult or impossible to organize complex systems or webs of trust."
(http://distributed-autonomous-society.quora.com/Decentralized-Law-and-the-DAS)


